heaviest_rainfall.status: Record amounts of rain fell over 31.0 hours today with a total accumulation of 23.86mm.  It fell at 8.3 mm per hour at times and ranked 7th from our records.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: There was a torrential downpour today where the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.6mm per hour (ranked 2nd in our records).  The storm lasted 2.6 hours and 6.1mm of precipitation fell during that time.  The rain rate reached 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: Ranked 7th for lengthiest precipitation event, today's storm spanned 31.0 hours and was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  23.86mm of rain fell in total.  A relentless rainstorm took place on 09 November 2025, it lasted 144.8 hours and it delivered 47.89mm of rain at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour.
